Three clubs have already booked their place in the last 16 of this year’s UEFA Champions League following the conclusion of Match Day 4 fixtures on Thursday night. They are: Bayern Munich, Juventus and Paris Saint-Germain. Bayern Munich progressed into the next round, following an incredible 2-0 win over Olympiacos on Thursday night. Juventus defeated Lokomotiv Moscow 2-1 in Russia, thanks to goals from Aaron Ramsey and Douglas Costa. Paris Saint-Germain also advanced to the knock out stage with two games to spare after beating Club Brugge 1-0 at home. The thirteen remaining teams will be decided on Match Day 5 (November 26 and 27) and Match Day 6 (December 10 and 11) respectively. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.